The eThekwini municipality is at pains to sort out all damaged infrastructure. Major wastewater plants have been damaged in flooding over a month ago. This caused havoc in many areas. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports. #DStv403 DURBAN - There's still a long way to go before KwaZulu-Natal will be back to normal following the devastating floods. Officials say they're trying their best to deal with all the problems and rebuild again. READ: KZN floods | Several beaches face extended closures But sewage and wastewater plants have been damaged. They say that will take time and money to fix. READ: Communities still feeling effects of KZN floods Meanwhile, beaches in Durban remain closed. E. coli levels remain alarmingly high with a huge risk of airborne diseases. * eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports.